<item>
            <title>[OAK-220] PropertyState can only be accessed from parent tree</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-220</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;currently the oak api only allows to access a given property state from&lt;br/&gt;
the parent tree. however the jcr api also allows to access properties&lt;br/&gt;
directly from the session object (see also &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-218&quot; title=&quot;Session methods rely on accessibility of root node&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-218&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-218&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) and we should/cannot not&lt;br/&gt;
rely on the accessibility of the parent node.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;possible solutions include for example adding Root#getProperty(String path)&lt;br/&gt;
in analogy to Root#getTree.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
