                            <comment id="13435235" author="mduerig" created="Wed, 15 Aug 2012 15:59:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See Jukka&apos;s proposal on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-212&quot; title=&quot;Tree#getPropertyStatus requires tree to exist&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-212&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-212&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. I think this is how we should proceed here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13435243" author="anchela" created="Wed, 15 Aug 2012 16:07:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fine with me... as commented in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-212&quot; title=&quot;Tree#getPropertyStatus requires tree to exist&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-212&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-212&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; having all those extra methods&lt;br/&gt;
on root looks a bit awkward to me. nevertheless i prefer having a&lt;br/&gt;
solution here and we may still refactor the API later on... given&lt;br/&gt;
the fact that we make use of jukka&apos;s NodeUtil all over the place in&lt;br/&gt;
oak i have the impression that we will add minor modifications here&lt;br/&gt;
or there... let&apos;s see how it evolves.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;btw: accessing properties independent of the parent is also needed&lt;br/&gt;
for the the reference stuff... keeping jukka&apos;s proposal in mind i&lt;br/&gt;
defined the corresponding manager to return property-oak-paths.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13441249" author="mduerig" created="Fri, 24 Aug 2012 15:28:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This should be solvable/fixed with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-275&quot; title=&quot;Introduce TreeLocation interface&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-275&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-275&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
